author: butek
msg: This is the final step in making stubs thread safe.
1.  Move setMaintainSession from Call object to Service object. (did yesterday)
2.  Each stub method must instantiate a new Call object (done here).
One question left.  Should the transport info stay in the Call object?  Or should it
move to the Server object?  (It's the transport that keeps the session.)  Since users
can call Call.setTargetEndpointAddress, the transport info should probably stay in
Call, but that's just my opinion.
